
Overview of noun herd

The noun herd has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (5) herd -- (a group of cattle or sheep or other domestic mammals all of the same kind that are herded by humans)
2. (2) herd -- (a group of wild mammals of one species that remain together: antelope or elephants or seals or whales or zebra)
3. ruck, herd -- (a crowd especially of ordinary or undistinguished persons or things; "his brilliance raised him above the ruck"; "the children resembled a fairy herd")

Overview of verb herd

The verb herd has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) herd, crowd -- (cause to herd, drive, or crowd together; "We herded the children into a spare classroom")
2. (1) herd -- (move together, like a herd)
3. herd -- (keep, move, or drive animals; "Who will be herding the cattle when the cowboy dies?")
